cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with 3D shape reconstruction from multi-modal data, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of level set methods and radial basis functions suggests a machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) approach. Finally, the use of diverse modalities such as volume slices and shape silhouettes suggests a multimedia (MM) aspect to the paper. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
